# Numeric input keyboards

When adding or editing **number-only** fields (dimensions, grades, percentages, elevations, counts, coordinates as typed values, etc.), set the platform keyboard to **numeric** or **decimal** by default. Do not leave the default text keyboard unless the field also accepts letters.

## When this applies

- Labels/units imply numbers: ft, %, grade, slope, width, elevation, chainage, angle (numeric), etc.
- `parseDouble`, `toInt`, `KeyboardType`, or validation expecting numeric input
- **Not** for: names, codes, CSV paths, search, passwords, free text notes

## Platform defaults

### Jetpack Compose (Android/Kotlin)

```kotlin
import androidx.compose.foundation.text.KeyboardOptions
import androidx.compose.ui.text.input.KeyboardType

OutlinedTextField(
    value = value,
    onValueChange = onValueChange,
    keyboardOptions = KeyboardOptions(keyboardType = KeyboardType.Decimal),
)
```

- Use **`KeyboardType.Decimal`** when values can include a decimal point (grades, feet, %).
- Use **`KeyboardType.Number`** only for integers (counts, whole feet if no fractions).

### Web (HTML / React / Vue)

```html
<input type="number" inputmode="decimal" step="any" />
```

```tsx
<input type="number" inputMode="decimal" step="any" />
```

### React Native

```tsx
<TextInput keyboardType="decimal-pad" />
```

### Flutter

```dart
keyboardType: const TextInputType.numberWithOptions(decimal: true),
```

### SwiftUI (iOS)

```swift
.keyboardType(.decimalPad) // or .numberPad for integers
```

## Checklist for agents

- [ ] Every new numeric `TextField` / `OutlinedTextField` / `<input>` has an explicit numeric `keyboardType` / `keyboardOptions` / `inputMode`
- [ ] Prefer **decimal** when the parser accepts floats (`parseDouble`, `0.3`, `12.5`)
- [ ] Apply the same keyboard to related fields in one form (e.g. min grade, max grade, width, cross-slope)
